      "writtenOn": "2021-07-15T20:02:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I notice this function no longer works correctly if the parser is pointing at a TK_CONST. Callers now check for TK_CONST and just call varDeclarations() directly if they see it.\n\nUnfortunately, this change makes the name \"varDeclarationsOrExpressionStatement\" kind of untrue. It works for expression-statements and for a SUBSET of var-declarations, but varDeclarations() can now handle some decls that varDeclarationsOrExpressionStatement() will not handle.\n\nThis seems brittle. Based on the function\u0027s name it should really be able to support everything that `varDeclarations()` can support.\n\nWe could assert that the next token isn\u0027t a TK_CONST and add a comment saying the caller needs to handle that case, but is that better than just actually handling it here? And if we actually handle TK_CONST here, that\u0027s just bringing it back to how it was in the original Parser...\n\nI\u0027m open to other ideas as well.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 361,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 361,
        "endChar": 4
      },
      "revId": "a3f8f7f8e5d95aed8e7a7b3fac486721f0aeca84",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
